 United Kingdom":"Bourton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Poure","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Galician and Portuguese: habitational name from any of the places called Moure, from the Latin personal name <i>Maurus</i>.","French: dialect variant of   More   ‘Moor’."],"variants":[{"name":"More","meanings":["1  Scottish, English:  see  Moore  ."]},{"name":"Mourey","meanings":["French: derivative of   Moure   ‘Moor’."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":36,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Poure was born in 1346, in Bourton, Oxfordshire, England, his father, William Poure, was 25 and his mother, Abigail Danewyke, was 20. He married Joan Burton in 1376. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 29 November 1398, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1346–29 Nov 1398":"1346–29. november 1398","1346–1398":"1346–1398","1350–1406":"1350–1406","1379–1443":"1379–1443","1387–1407":"1387–1407","1321–Male":"13